  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Advocacy, Communications and Capacity Strengthening in Latin America for more equitable societies</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project supports CAFOD&#x2019;s long term partner Comunicaciones Aliadas (COAL) in the implementation of one of its strategic objectives set by the organisation for 2018-2022, which relates to the production of information and analysis on environmental rights, to inform public advocacy work across Latin America. This project is a direct continuation of the previous projects that CAFOD has held with this partner. 

The project will begin with a basic mapping of the main social advocacy processes for environmental rights in the region to determine the main issues that will need to be addressed in the thematic news series that COAL will produce. Subsequently, COAL will coordinate with their news correspondents the production process of the relevant articles (published biweekly) while COAL&apos;s news team will produce short notes that will accompany the thematic series. In addition to the thematic series, COAL will also produce infographics, one for each of the themes of the series.

All information will be produced in Spanish and will be disseminated on the institutional website, Comunicaciones Aliadas, as well as on COAL&apos;s Facebook.</narrative>
  </description>
